THIRD-PARTY KEYBOARD FIRMWARE — INTEROPERABILITY
------------------------------------------------
Remappr configures and exchanges data with several keyboard-firmware projects.
It does NOT include, link against, or redistribute their source code. Remappr's
firmware support is implemented from public protocol specifications and the
public, over-the-wire keycode and command numbering those projects expose
(interface facts) — and it EMITS configuration / project files that the user
compiles with the respective firmware's own toolchain. Any GPL obligations
attaching to a firmware binary built from that emitted output fall on whoever
builds and distributes that binary, not on Remappr itself.

  - ZMK Firmware — MIT License
        https://github.com/zmkfirmware/zmk
  - QMK Firmware — GNU GPL v2
        https://github.com/qmk/qmk_firmware
  - VIA — GNU GPL v2 (protocol spec)
        https://www.caniusevia.com/docs/specification
  - Vial — GNU GPL v2 / v3
        https://get.vial.today
  - Keychron QMK fork — GNU GPL v2
        https://github.com/Keychron/qmk_firmware
  - Keyboard Layout Editor (KLE) serial format / kle-serial — MIT License
        Copyright (c) Ian Prest — https://github.com/ijprest/kle-serial
        (the KLE label-map table and deserializer in src/firmware/kle/parser.ts)

The respective marks (ZMK, QMK, VIA, Vial, Keychron) belong to their owners and
are used here for identification and interoperability only; their use does not
imply endorsement by, or affiliation with, those projects.


